    "## 4. Inheritance and Overriding Methods\n",
    "Inheritance allows us to define a class that inherits all the methods and properties from another class.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Why:\n",
    "We use inheritance to create a specific class from a general one, sharing common functionality while adding specific details.\n",
    "\n",
    "### What:\n",
    "Here, we define a `vehicle` class and then create a subclass `bmw` that inherits from it.\n",
    "\n",
    "### How: Syntax\n",
    "A subclass is created using the following syntax:\n",
    "```python\n",
    "class SubClassName(ParentClassName):\n",
    "    def __init__(self, params):\n",
    "        super().__init__(parent_params)\n",
    "```\n",
    "We also override the parent class methods in the subclass if needed."
   ]
